Looking ahead from Week 25, several processes were already in motion. The class\uc0\u8209 action lawsuits over birthright citizenship and the ideological deportation policy would test whether courts would continue to draw lines around the Fourteenth Amendment and free speech. The lawsuits over vaccine policy and Planned Parenthood funding would determine how far administrative law could constrain ideologically driven health decisions. The State Department\'92s rolling layoffs, enabled by the Supreme Court, would continue to shrink diplomatic capacity in the weeks to come. The dismantling of FEMA and DHS oversight offices, if carried through, would leave future disasters and detention conditions even more exposed to political whim. The August 1 tariff deadline loomed as a moment when emergency\u8209 based trade policy could harden into a new normal. And the IRS\'92s church\u8209 endorsement policy, once tested in court, would either be entrenched or checked, with lasting consequences for the role of religion in electoral politics.\
